{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, Marcus highlighted how heavy rains lead to pit latrine damage and collapse in Kenya's Lake Victoria Basin [44].",
    "In Rio de Janeiro, Libertun de Duren et al.",
    "found that sewerage systems overflowed during heavy rains, but this was also caused by population growth overtaking the capacity of the sanitation system [59].",
    "In Cox's Bazar, Bangladesh, Mitu et al.",
    "reported that heavy rains, flash floods, and landslides caused waterlogging as drainage systems were not regularly cleared [58]."
  ]
}